body.p:
By default, line wrapping does not apply on inline elements, which could cause some lines
      of code to bleed out of the page. To allow line wrapping, the property should be set on the
      parent block with the following rule in your customization
        CSS:*:has(*[class ~= 'pr-d/codeph']) {
  overflow-wrap: break-word;
}


It is possible to use hyphens: auto instead of overflow-wrap:
              break-word.

It is possible to use the same rule for software domain elements (e.g.
              filepath or cmdname).
